Aarmored calvary regiment?

cal*va*ry
1.A sculptured depiction of the Crucifixion. 
2.calvary A great ordeal. 

cav*al*ry
1.A highly mobile army unit using vehicular transport, such as light armor
and helicopters. 
2.Troops trained to fight on horseback. 

Sorry. . . One of by big pet peeves. It's one of those words like "anemone"
that most people mis-pronounce AND mis-spell.

